  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "from Havilah until thou comest to Shur",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The region occupied by the Ishmaelites is described in the same terms in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 25:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Havilah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is supposed to be a district of Arabia, but its position cannot be fixed with any certainty. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Shur",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is repeatedly mentioned in connexion with the route from Palestine to Egypt, and appears to be the part of the Arabian desert bordering on Egypt. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 16:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 20:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 15:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 27:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Shur",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " means ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "wall",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the name may have been derived from the wall which anciently defended the north-eastern frontier of Egypt.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
