  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 7.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "From Havilah until thou comest to Shur.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Hebrew, \"from Havilah as thou goest towards Shur.\" It seems impossible that this Havilah can be the northwestern portion of Yemen, called Chawlan, and identified with the Havilah of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 10:7, 29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as this would make Saul smite them from southeast to northwest. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Shur",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which means ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "wall",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is, as Wellhausen (Text 1 samuel 9:7) observes, originally the name of the wall which ran from Pelusium past Migdol to Hero, and which gave to Egypt, as Ebers thinks, its name Mizraim, the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "enclosed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "fortified.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Shur is again mentioned in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 27:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as indicating the direction towards Egypt of the region occupied by the Amalekites. Havilah, which means ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "circle",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", must have been some spot on the route to the isthmus of Suez, lying on the edge of the wilderness to the south of Judah, where Saul commenced his foray. Beginning thus upon the borders of Judaea, Saul continued his devastations up to the limits of Egypt. 1 Samuel 15:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Saul directed the Kenites to come out from among the Amalekites, that they might not perish with them (אספך, imp. Kal of אסף), as they had shown affection to the Israelites on their journey out of Egypt (compare ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 10:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 1:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). He then smote the Amalekites from Havilah in the direction towards Shur, which lay before (to the east of) Egypt (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 25:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Shur is the desert of Jifar, i.e., that portion of the desert of Arabia which borders upon Egypt (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 16:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Havilah, the country of the Chaulotaeans, on the border of Arabia Petraea towards Yemen (see at ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 10:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ").",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]